$ Overpass Turbo IDE extensions for the Overpass API

The Overpass Turbo IDE has some extensions to assist formulating queries for the → development/OpenStreetMap/API/Overpass.

table { ll

  → development/OpenStreetMap/API/Overpass/extensions/bbox[`{{bbox}}`] ☰ Calculate a bounding box based on current map view bounding box coordinates of the current map view
  `{{center}}`                   ☰ Calculate center coordinates of current map view map center coordinates
  `{{date}}`                     ☰ Current date and time
  `{{date:specifier}}`           ☰ Create historical date based on specifier. Syntax is a number followed by a time period: second, minute, hour, days, weeks, months, years. E.g. 1 day, 2 years
  `{{date:…}}`                   ☰ → misc/ISO/8601 date-time-string a certain time interval ago (e.g. “24 hours”)
  `{{geocodeId:"query"}}`        ☰ Perform → development/OpenStreetMap/Nominatim search using query. Use OSM id of first result
  `{{→ development/OpenStreetMap/API/Overpass/extensions/geocode#overpass-geocodeArea[geocodeArea]:"query"}}`      ☰ Perform Nominatim search using query for an area. Use OSM id of first area
  `{{geocodeBbox:"query"}}`      ☰ Perform Nominatim search using query. Use the bounding box of the first result
  `{{geocodeCoords:"query"}}`    ☰ Perform Nominatim search using query. Use the centroid of the first result
  → development/OpenStreetMap/API/Overpass/extensions/style[`{{style:…}}`] ☰  Define MapCSS stylesheet which specify how a query result is (graphically) rendered.
  `{{var=val}}` ☰ Define a variable named `var`. `{{var}}` will be relpaced by `val` in the query.
  `{{data:overpass,server=...}}` ☰ Specify → development/web/URI-URL-URN-IRI-URC#url[URL] of Overpass API endpoint

table }
